function keep_only_names(words::Vector{String})
    return filter(word -> startswith(uppercasefirst(word), uppercase('A')), words)
end
```

This function uses the `filter` higher-order function to iteratively apply a predicate to each element of `words`. The predicate checks if the first letter of the word (converted to uppercase) is greater than or equal to 'A'. This ensures that only words starting with a capital letter are kept.
